The ANC’s KwaZulu-Natal provincial executive committee held a special meeting to discuss the fate of embattled eThekwini mayor Zandile Gumede. • Editor’s note: This livestream has ended. You may watch the recording above DURBAN -The ANC in KwaZulu-Natal has axed the leadership of the Msunduzi and eThekwini municipalities, relieving both Themba Njilo and Zandile Gumede of their current duties. This after the KZN provincial executive committee held a special meeting to discuss the fate of embattled eThekwini mayor Zandile Gumede. READ: eThekwini municipality in for major shake-up, say sources On Monday, sources at the meeting said Gumede will be axed. They also said that the entire executive committee must vacate their positions.